President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 8, 2016, as Mother's Day in the United States. In the proclamation, he recognizes the important role that mothers play in our lives and the impact they have on shaping who we become as adults. He emphasizes the need to support and empower working mothers and highlights the efforts his administration has made to expand child care, strengthen paid leave, and close the gender pay gap. The proclamation also calls on all Americans to express love and gratitude to mothers everywhere and to observe Mother's Day with appropriate programs and activities.